  "retained_ready": false,
  "summary": "Focused audit of the apparent duplicate block_table_rows in native c3 full-attention metadata. The duplicates are expected row-relative physical-slot offsets from _batch_full_spans, not block-table corruption: for contiguous active slots, every row stores the same logical table because the kernels add the active row internally; when rowchunk2 runs a tail chunk with slot 2 as compact row 0, the expected row-relative table shifts to slot2 offsets. All audited c2/c3 native/rowchunk2 retained and L40 trace segments match this formula. Since active c2 is green with the same expected duplicate rows, duplicate block-table metadata is not sufficient to explain the c3 grouping>=3 red path. The fix target remains hidden/pre-QKV grouped full-attention behavior, not block-table construction.",
